{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"iddc458424-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06","identifier":"/us/usc/t12/s1773"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"1773"},"text":"§ 1773.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" District of Columbia credit unions; conversion to Federal status","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Any credit union organized under the District of Columbia Credit Unions Act, as amended, may apply for conversion into a Federal credit union by filing with the National Credit Union Administration Board (in sections 1773 to 1775 of this title referred to as the Board), pursuant to a resolution adopted by a majority of its directors, an organization certificate meeting the requirements of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1753"},"text":"section 1753 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"iddc458425-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/395/s1"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–395, § 1","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/377"},"text":"78 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/206/s3"},"text":"Pub. L. 91–206, § 3","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1970-03-10"},"text":"Mar. 10, 1970","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/84/49"},"text":"84 Stat. 49","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/630/tV/s501"},"text":"Pub. L. 95–630, title V, § 501","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1978-11-10"},"text":"Nov. 10, 1978","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/92/3680"},"text":"92 Stat. 3680","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"iddc458426-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"iddc458427-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"iddc458428-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The District of Columbia Credit Unions Act, referred to in text, was repealed by ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/395/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–395, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/377"},"text":"78 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"iddc458429-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was not enacted as part of the Federal Credit Union Act which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"statutoryNotes","id":"iddc45842a-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"transferOfFunctions","id":"iddc45842b-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Transfer of Functions","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“National Credit Union Administration Board” and “Board” substituted in text for “Director of the Bureau of Federal Credit Unions” and “Director”, respectively, pursuant to ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/91/206/s3"},"text":"section 3 of Pub. L. 91–206","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/630/s501"},"text":"section 501 of Pub. L. 95–630","children":[],"tail":" ["},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t12/s1752a"},"text":"12 U.S.C. 1752a","children":[],"tail":"] which transferred functions of Bureau of Federal Credit Unions, and Director thereof, to National Credit Union Administration and vested authority for management of Administration in National Credit Union Administration Board."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"repeals","id":"iddc45842c-3a6f-11f1-8fa0-c065796a7f06"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Repeals; Revocation of Organization Certificates Issued Under District of Columbia Credit Unions Act","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/395/s4"},"text":"Pub. L. 88–395, § 4","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/78/377"},"text":"78 Stat. 377","children":[],"tail":", provided that: "},{"tag":"quotedContent","attrib":{"origin":"/us/pl/88/395/s4"},"text":"“Effective thirty days after enactment of this Act [","children":[{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1964-08-01"},"text":"Aug. 1, 1964","children":[],"tail":"], the District of Columbia Credit Unions Act ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/47/326"},"text":"47 Stat. 326","children":[],"tail":"), as amended, is repealed and all organization certificates issued thereunder and still in force are revoked.”"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
